Example 3 – Data Cleaning and Standardization Agent

Poor Problem Statement

> “We need a Python Data Cleaning Agent.”



Why This Is Poor

No dataset context

No processing expectations

No validation criteria

No quality definition



---

Recommended Problem Statement

Business Problem

Data engineering teams spend significant manual effort performing repetitive data cleaning and transformation activities across structured datasets.

Current State

Teams receive CSV and Excel datasets from multiple upstream systems with:

Missing values

Inconsistent formats

Duplicate records

Invalid data types

Non-standard naming conventions


Most transformations follow repeatable patterns.

Desired Agent Capability

The Agent Hub solution should:

Analyze sample datasets

Infer cleaning patterns

Generate Python-based transformation logic

Recommend validation rules

Produce reusable cleaning pipelines


Inputs Available

Sample datasets

Data dictionaries

Existing transformation examples

Quality rules

Historical cleaning scripts


Expected Outputs

Python cleaning scripts

Transformation recommendations

Validation reports

Data quality summaries

Reusable processing workflows


Constraints

Must preserve auditability of transformations

Must not overwrite source datasets

Human approval required before production execution

Must comply with data governance standards


Success Criteria

Reduced manual data preparation effort

Increased consistency in cleaning operations

Reusable transformation pipelines

Improved data quality metrics



---

Common Anti-Patterns

Anti-Pattern	Why It Fails

“Build an AI developer”	Too broad
“Create a QA bot”	No workflow defined
“Automate BA activities”	No measurable outcome
“Use GenAI for data operations”	No business value definition
“Replace developers using agents”	Unrealistic and governance risk
Undefined autonomy	Creates operational risk
No human review process	Violates enterprise governance
No success metrics	Impossible to evaluate ROI



---

Recommended Agent Framing

Instead of defining agents by job titles, define them by workflow assistance.

Avoid	Prefer

QA Agent	Test Case Generation Assistant
UI Developer Agent	UI Component Generation Assistant
BA Agent	Requirement-to-Jira Transformation Assistant
Data Engineer Agent	Data Cleaning and Validation Assistant
PO Agent	Backlog Structuring Assistant



---

Final Guidance for Teams

Teams should focus on:

1. The workflow problem


2. Available inputs


3. Desired outputs


4. Governance constraints


5. Human approval steps


6. Measurable success criteria



The most successful Agent Hub use cases are not “AI replacing roles,” but targeted workflow accelerators embedded into existing enterprise processes.
